    "www.nature.com/scientificreports/",
    "• medium: This means that the code will detect craters that are between 5 and 15 pixels in diameter, which corresponds to craters between 1.25 and 3.75 km in real life.",
    "• small: This means that the code will detect craters that are less than 5 pixels in diameter, which corresponds to craters smaller than 1.25 km in real life.",
    "• large: This means that the code will detect craters that are larger than 15 pixels in diameter, which corresponds to craters larger than 3.75 km in real life.",
    "The Max detections parameter is used to limit the number of bounding boxes that the model predicts for each image."
